          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry and blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold butter into the flour and salt until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of cold water and mix to a firm dough. Flatten into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Preheat the oven to 200°C conventional. Roll the pastry to 3 mm thick and use it to line a 23 cm pie dish, leaving a 1 cm overhang. Line with baking paper and fill with baking beans. Bake for 15 minutes, remove the paper and beans, brush the base with beaten egg yolk, and bake for a further 5 minutes until the base is dry and pale gold. Reduce the oven to 180°C.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and bake the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the pumpkin purée, cream, sugar, eggs, egg yolk, spices, vanilla, and salt until completely smooth. Pour into the blind-baked case. Bake at 180°C for 40 to 45 minutes until the edges are fully set and the centre wobbles gently as a unit when the dish is moved. Leave to cool to room temperature, the filling firms further as it cools. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before slicing. Serve with lightly whipped cream.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
